Deadly shooting at New Castle park
You need Flash to watch this video.Sorry, your browser doesn't support Flash, needs a Flash update, or has Flash disabled.
Police in New Castle, Delaware are investigating a deadly shooting at a park. (WPVI)
Embed
<iframe width="476" height="267" src="http://6abc.com/video/embed/?pid=1309013" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
WPVI
Monday, April 25, 2016 11:31PM
NEW CASTLE, Del.
(WPVI) --
Police in New Castle, Delaware are investigating a deadly shooting at a park.The shooting happened shortly before 9 p.m. Monday at Surratte Park on the 400 block of Anderson Drive.
Responding officers arrived to find a man, believed to be in his late teens to early 20s, down on the street, suffering from at least one gunshot wound.He was pronounced dead at the scene.No suspects have been arrested.
